# python3-torch is intentionally NOT declared. The distro 'python3-torch'
# is CPU-only and unsuitable for GPU workloads; users install matching
# CUDA torch via pip — see packaging/INSTALL.md once published.
Recommends: python3-numpy
Provides: python3-flagtree, python3-triton
Conflicts: python3-triton, python3-flagtree-iluvatar, python3-flagtree-mthreads,
           python3-flagtree-metax, python3-flagtree-amd, python3-flagtree-cambricon,
           python3-flagtree-hcu, python3-flagtree-xpu
Replaces: python3-triton
# Note: Breaks: without a version is equivalent to Conflicts:; using
# Conflicts: above is enough (Debian Policy §7.4).
Description: FlagTree compiler with NVIDIA backend
 FlagTree is a unified compiler supporting multiple AI chip backends for
 custom Deep Learning operations, forked from triton-lang/triton.
 .
 This package contains the FlagTree Python distribution built with the NVIDIA
 backend enabled. It installs into the "triton" Python namespace and conflicts
 with the upstream python3-triton package.
 .
 Requires CUDA runtime to execute kernels on NVIDIA GPUs at runtime.
